<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Public Citizen Litigation Group Home Page</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#0000ff" ALINK="#ff0000" 
VLINK="#dd0000">

<H1><CENTER><IMG HEIGHT=160 WIDTH=240 SRC="/public_citizen/pclogo.gif" 
ALT="PUBLIC
 CITIZEN">
</CENTER></H1>
<H1><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+4>T</FONT>HE  <FONT
SIZE=+4>L</FONT>ITIGATION
<FONT SIZE=+4>G</FONT>ROUP
</CENTER></H1>
<BR>
<p>

<CENTER>
<table border width=100% cellpadding=5>
<tr><td><a href="http://www.citizen.org/public_citizen/litigation/annual_rep/1995.html">1995
Litigation Group
Annual Report</a>
<td><a href="http://www.citizen.org/public_citizen/litigation/brief.html">Briefs, Testimony,
and
Memoranda</a>
<td><a href="http://www.citizen.org/public_citizen/litigation/foic/foic.html">The Freedom of
Information Clearinghouse</a><tr><td><a
href="http://www.citizen.org/public_citizen/litigation/scap/scap.html">Supreme Court Assitance
Project</a>
<td><a 
href="gopher://gopher.essential.org/hh/ftp/pub/public_citizen/pclg">Gopher 
Site</a>
<td><a 
href="http://www.citizen.org/public_citizen/litigation/current.html">Current
Issues</a><img 
src="/public_citizen/litigation/graphics/new01.gif"></table> </CENTER>


<P>
Public Citizen Litigation Group is a 10-lawyer public interest law
firm that was founded by Ralph Nader and Alan Morrison in 1972.  It engages 
in a wide variety of public interest litigation in federal circuit and  
state courts around the country.<BR>  

<P><A HREF="/public_citizen/litigation/annual_rep/1995.html">The 1995
Public Citizen Litigation Group Annual Report</a> describes the
Litigation Group's work in detail. 
<P><A HREF="/public_citizen/litigation/scap/scap.html">
The Litigation Group's Supreme Court Assistance Project</a> helps
small
firm practitioners, legal services lawyers, and other lawyers with
little
or no experience in Supreme Court litigation.  Public Citizen
Litigation
Group attorneys have argued 38 cases in the Supreme Court.   
<P><A HREF="/public_citizen/litigation/foic/foic.html">
The Freedom of Information Clearinghouse</a> provides technical and
legal assistance to individuals, public interest groups, and the
media who
seek access to information held by government agencies through the
Freedom
of Information Act, the Privacy Act, the Federal Advisory Committee
Act,
and other laws.
<P>Public Citizen Litigation Group
<A HREF="/public_citizen/litigation/brief.html"> Briefs and Other 
Materials by Topic.</a><BR>  
This link contains a menu containing briefs, memoranda,
testimony, and
other records reflecting the Litigation Group's work in various
areas,
including the enforcement of the open government laws (i.e. the
Freedom of
Information Act, the Privacy Act, the Federal Advisory Committee
Act, and
common law and constitutional doctrines concerning open court
records),
the failure of administrative agencies to carry out statutory
mandates,
particularly in the health and safety area, union democracy and
workers'
rights, separation of powers, and a variety of other general
consumer and
general government accountability cases.
  

<P>[    Go to the <A
HREF="/public_citizen/public_citizen.html"><IMG WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=20
SRC="/public_citizen/pclogo.gif" ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="**">Public Citizen Home
Page]</A><BR>
<HR>
<P>
Send questions or comments about the Litigation Group Home Page
to:<BR>
<ADDRESS> the Litigation Group<A
HREF="mailto:LitigationGroup@citizen.org">&lt;litigationgroup@citizen.org></A>
</ADDRESS>

</BODY>

</HTML>
