<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>What's New at Critical Mass</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000ff"
VLINK="#dd0000"
ALINK="#ff0000">
<H3><CENTER>What's New on the Critical Mass Web
Page?</CENTER></H3>
<P>
<UL>
<LI>December 10, 1996<A
HREF="/orgs/public_citizen/CMEP/restructuring/comments/ipalco.html">
Comments to Nuclear Regulatory Commission</A> regarding the impact of
competition and electric utility industry restructuring on its power
reactor licensees.
<P>

<LI>December 4, 1996
<A HREF="/CMEP/nuclearsafety/120496comments.html">Comments Before the Nuclear
Regulatory Commission</A> 
regarding the Strategic Assessment and Re-baselining Project 
<P>

<LI>October 9, 1996 <A 
HREF="/CMEP/nuclearsafety/lemon-summary.html">"Nuclear Lemons 5th 
Edition: An Assessment of America's Worst Commercial Nuclear Power 
Plants" </A>Nuclear Lemons determines the worst commercial nuclear 
reactors based on twelve safety, economic, and performance indicators.  
The rankings are based entirely on statistics garnered from government and 
industry documents.  The <A 
HREF="/CMEP/nuclearsafety/lemons-release.html">Press release </A> 
states that the Nuclear Regulatory Agency has failed to 
identify many of the most troubled nuclear reactors in the nation. The 
Reactor-by-Reactor 
Data Supplement contains a breakdown of each reactor's performance based on 
the criteria used in Nuclear Lemons. Includes complete data used to rank plants 
along with other useful site specific information.<P> 

<LI>August 21, 1996 The <A 
HREF="/CMEP/restructuring/restructuring.html">Electricity Restructuring 
Clearinghouse </A>has been opened and will continue to be expanded.  Our 
report summary of <A HREF="/CMEP/pubs/blueprintsummary.html">Power for the 
People,</A> an public interest 
blueprint for electricity restructuring, is included in this new section. 
<P> 
<LI>August 2, 1996 -- 
A <A 
HREF="/CMEP/radwaste/080196update.html">list</A> of how Senators voted on 
S. 1936 is in the updates section of Radioactive Waste Policy.
<P>
<LI>July 31, 
1996 -- The Senate passed S. 1936, but failed to secure veto-proof numbers.  
The <A HREF="/CMEP/radwaste/073196release.html">release</A> is in the updates 
section of Radioactive Waste Policy.
<P>
<LI>July 29, 1996 -- Two current energy 
policy <A HREF="/CMEP/072996jobannouncement.html">job announcements</A>.
<P>
<LI>July 26, 1996 -- S. 1936 will be <A 
HREF="/CMEP/radwaste/072696update.html">on the floor</A> on Wednesday.  
The update is in the Radioactive Waste Policy section.
<P>
<LI>July 25, 1996 -- An <A 
HREF="/CMEP/renewables/072596update.html">update</A> on the House vote on 
three safe energy amendments to the Energy And Water Appropriations Bill 
is available in the Renewable Energy Update Section.
<P>
<LI>July 23, 1996 -- An <A HREF="/CMEP/budget/071996e+w.html">alert</A> 
on the Energy and Water Appropriations Bill is available in the Polluter 
Pork and Renewable Energy Update sections.
<P> 
<LI>July 17, 1996 -- An <A 
HREF="/CMEP/radwaste/071796update.html">update</A> on the first Senate 
waste bill vote is in the Update section of Radioactive Waste 
Policy.
<P>
<LI>July 1, 1996 -- Read about <A 
HREF="/CMEP/070196changes.html">changes</A> in Critical Mass' staff.
<P>
<LI>June 
27, 1996 
-- <A HREF="/CMEP/nuclearsafety/062796comments.html">Comments</A> before 
the Federal Radiological Preparadness Coordinating Committee's Ad Hoc 
Subcommittee on Potassium Iodide are available in the Nuclear Power 
and Reactor Safety Updates section.
<P>
<LI>June 27, 1996 -- Public Citizen has released a report on renewable 
energy programs.  Read the <A 
HREF="/CMEP/renewables/062796source.html">release</A> in the Renewable 
Energy Updates section.  
<P>
<LI>An <A HREF="/CMEP/transportation/062796alert.html">alert</A> on the 
anti-CAFE rider to the House Appropriations bill in available in the Update 
section of Transportation and Fuel Economy.
<P>
<LI>June 25, 
1996 -- A <A HREF="/CMEP/transportation/062596letter.html">letter</A> to 
Representatives opposing a FY97 Transportation Appropriations Bill 
anti-CAFE rider is available in the Update section of Transportation and 
Fuel Economy.
<P>
<LI>June 20, 1996 -- Public Citizen has released a Blueprint for 
electricity industry restructuring.  Read the <A 
HREF="/CMEP/restructuring/archive/062096release.html">release</A> and press 
conference <A 
HREF="/CMEP/restructuring/archive/062096statement.html">statement</A> in the 
Update sections of Renewable Energy and Energy Efficiency.
<P>
<LI>June 13, 1996 -- A <A 
HREF="/CMEP/nuclearsafety/061396france.html">survey</A> of French 
citizen's views on nuclear power is available in the Update section of Nuclear 
Power and Reactor Safety.
<P>
<LI>May 28, 1996 -- A <A 
HREF="/CMEP/transportation/052896letter.html">letter</A> to the Chairman 
of the House Appropriations Committee on federal transit funding is 
available in the Update section of Transportation and Fuel Economy.
<P> 
<LI>May 28, 1996 -- A <A HREF="/CMEP/radwaste/050996letter.html">letter</A> 
to the House on the Texas Low Level Compact is available in the Update 
section of Radioactive Waste Policy.
<P>
<LI>May 22, 1996 -- 69 Representatives signed a <A 
HREF="/CMEP/budget/052296alwr.html">letter</A> in opposition to the ALWR 
program.  The letter can be found in the Update section of Polluter Pork. 
<P>
<LI>May 6, 1996 -- A press conference <A 
HREF="/CMEP/transportation/050296statement.html">statement</A> on rising 
gasoline prices is in the update portion of the Transportation section.
<P> 
<LI>April 30, 1996 -- An article on the <A 
HREF="/CMEP/nuclearsafety/043096oped.html">lessons of Chernobyl</A> is in 
the Nuclear Safety Section.
<P> 
<LI>April 8, 1996 -- An <A 
HREF="/CMEP/efficiency/040596eff.html">update</A> on appliance efficiency 
standards is available in the updates section of Energy Efficiency.
<P>
<LI>April 2, 1996 -- A new <A HREF="/CMEP/radwaste/nwtrb1271.html">fact 
sheet</A> comparing the Senate nuclear waste bill to recommendations by 
the Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board is available in the Radioactive 
Waste Policy Fact Sheets section.
<P>
<LI>March 20, 1996 -- <A 
HREF="/CMEP/budget/032096doe.html">Information</A> on 
DOE's FY '97 budget request is available.
<P>
<LI>March 19, 1996 -- An <A 
HREF="/CMEP/nuclearsafety/031896letter.html">update</A> on the effects of 
the product liability bill is in the Nuclear Power and Reactor Safety 
section.
<P>
<LI>March 
14, 1996 -- Updates on the <A 
HREF="/CMEP/radwaste/031396.html">radioactive waste bills</A> and the <A 
HREF="/CMEP/nuclearsafety/031396salem.html">Salem reactor</A> in the 
Radioactive Waste Policy and Reactor Safety sections.
<P>
<LI>March 5, 1996 -- A direct link to the <A 
HREF="http://www.essential.org/orgs/FOE/scissors96">Green Scissors</A> 
report is available in the Polluter Pork section.
<P>
<LI>March 1, 1996 -- Critical Mass' <A 
HREF="/CMEP/022996test.html">testimony</A> to the House Energy and Water 
Appropriations Subcommittee is available in the testimony sections 
of Renewable Energy and Polluter Pork.
<P> 
<LI>February 19, 1996 -- An <A 
HREF="/CMEP/radwaste/021996ward.html">update</A> on the proposed Ward 
Valley dump is available in the update section of Radioactive Waste Policy.
<P>
<LI>February 15, 1996 -- The <A HREF="/CMEP/budget/021596green.html">Press 
Release for the Green Scissors Report</A> is available in the update 
section of Cutting Polluter Pork.
<P>
<LI>February 7, 1996 -- Critical 
Mass' <A HREF="/CMEP/votingindex/votes.html">Congressional Voting
Index</A> is on line.
<P>
<LI>February 7, 1996 -- Read Energy America Education Fund's <A
HREF="/CMEP/candidatespoll.html">1996 U.S. Presidential
Candidates Environmental & Energy Issues Questionnaire</A>.
<P>
</UL>
