<HTML><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000ff" 
VLINK="#dd0000"
ALINK="#ff0000">
<BODY> <CENTER><H3>
<FONT SIZE=+2>O</FONT>THER <FONT SIZE=+2>I</FONT>NTERNET <FONT 
SIZE=+2>R</FONT>ESOURCES</H3></CENTER> <P>
Use this page to link with other sustainable energy policy resources on the 
internet.
<P>
<em>What have we missed?</em>
<P>If you know an internet link that should be on 
this page,
let us know by emailing us at <ADDRESS><A 
HREF="mailto:cmep@essential.org">CMEP@Essential.org</A></ADDRESS> <P>
<CENTER><strong>
Advocacy</strong></CENTER>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.biomass.org/">Biomass Energy Alliance</A> -- A
clearinghouse for information about biomass fuels and their 
environmental benefits.  Subsections include a legislative alerts and 
links to related pages. <P>
<A HREF="http://www.deev.com/ccnr">Canadian Coalition for Nuclear 
Responsibility</A> -- A Canadian site on nuclear issues.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.ceert.org">Center for Energy Efficiency and 
Renewable Technologies</A> -- A California based efficiency and renewable 
energy site.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.pic.net/~stevie2/pages/cemail.html">Electronic 
Lobbyist</A> -- This site allows users to 
automatically send messages promoting renewable energy to their Members 
of Congress.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.essential.org/FOE/FOE.html">Friends of the 
Earth</A> <P>
<A HREF="http://www.greenpeace.org/">Greenpeace</A> -- Greenpeace's home 
page.  Contains alerts, releases, and other information plus numerous 
links to related sites
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.rmi.org/">Rocky Mountain Institute</A> -- RMI's 
home 
page.  A leader in sustainable resource use and energy efficiency practices.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.nwenergy.org/ncac">Northwest Conservation Act 
Coalition</A> -- 
<P>

<A HREF="http://www.nci.org/nci/">Nuclear Control Institute</A> 
-- NCI is an independent research and advocacy center specializing in 
problems of nuclear proliferation.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.nirs.org">NIRS</A> -- 
Nuclear Information and Resource Service.  NIRS is an information and 
networking center for citizens and environmental organizations concerned 
about nuclear power, radioactive waste, radiation, and sustainable energy 
issues.  Their page contains updates, alerts, factsheets, and information 
about NRC actions.
<P> 
<A HREF="http://solstice.crest.org/">Solstice</A>
-- An excellent clearinghouse of renewable energy information.
<P>
<A HREF="http://miya.ecn.fpu.ac.jp/monju-a2e.htm">Stop the Monju 
Reactor</A> -- An online petition to stop the Japanese fast breeder 
reactor.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.ucsusa.org">Union of Concerned Scientists</A> 
 -- Environmentally sound scientists with a section on energy policy.
<P>
<A HREF="http://antenna.nl/user/wise/">World Information Service on 
Energy (WISE)</A> 
-- The World Information Service on
Energy (WISE, Amsterdam)  covers nuclear safety issues including 
health and environmental impacts of reactor safety, nuclear waste 
issues and uranium mining and milling. <P>
<CENTER><strong>
Government</strong></CENTER>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.energy.ca.gov/energy">California Energy Commission</A> --
Contains subsections dedicated to alternative and renewable energy, 
alternatively fueled autos,
agriculture and energy, California energy systems, and tips on cutting energy 
bills.  The page
offers links to various other governmental and advocacy groups' internet pages.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.eren.doe.gov">Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy
Network</A> -- Locates and organizes qualitative information on renewable
energy
technologies, energy efficiency, and Federal energy management programs.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/">Environmental Protection Agency Public 
Access
Server</A>
-- A clearinghouse and index of EPA files and documents.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.nrel.gov/">National Renewable Energy Laboratory</A> 
-- A
clearinghouse of information on renewable energy technology.  The page 
offers
both NREL
documents and files as well as a directory of related web pages, and an
information search
option.  Contains subsections on alternative fuels, photovoltaics, wind
technology, and
industrial technology.
<P>
<A HREF="http://raleigh.dis.anl.gov/">Office of 
Human Radiation Experiments</A> --
Information on human radiation experiments.  Contains updates, press releases,
a D.O.E.
declassified file search, and links to the D.O.E., advocacy groups, and the 
White House.
<P>
<A HREF="http://thomas.loc.gov">Thomas</A> -- Access to legislation text, the
<em>Congressional Record</em>, and other legislative resources.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/text/government/legislative_branch/">
Yahoo -- Legislative
Branch</A> -- A clearinghouse of legislative information, contains a broad 
range of resources.
<P>
<CENTER><strong>
Educational</strong></CENTER>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.pv.unsw.edu.au/">Center for Photovoltaic 
Devices
and Systems</A> -- This clearinghouse of solar technology information is 
run
by the School of Electronic Engineering at the University of New South
Wales, and offers a list of CPDS publications, press releases, a list of
links to related pages, and a list of e-mail addresses of researchers
involved in solar technology.
<P>
<A HREF="http://zebu.uoregon.edu/energy.html">Energy and the 
Environment</A>
 -- An
educational forum sponsored by the University of Oregon, focusing on 
energy and
environmental issues. Offers on-line classes on energy and the 
environment and
alternative
energy sources.  Also offers a directory to other related links on the 
internet.
<P>
<A 
HREF="http://teaparty.terc.edu/energy/energy.html.">Energy Net</A> -- 
Energy Net is a network science project that allows students to evaluate 
their schools' energy use (ie. lighting
and heating systems) and share their information over the internet.  The page 
also offers a clearinghouse of information on renewable energy, energy 
efficiency, and energy policy. 
<P>
