<html>
<head>
<title>Public Citizen: Help Pass the NAFTA
Accountability Act!</title>
<meta name="Public Citizen" content="WP Internet Publisher 6.1">
</head>
<body>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#dd0000" A
LINK="#ff0000"><p>

<center><img src="http://www.citizen.org/images/pclogo.gif" width="120" 
height="100" ALT="PUBLIC CITIZEN"><p>

<h1></center>
<center>Help Pass the NAFTA Accountability Act!</h1>
<b></b><a href="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/activism/topten.html">Ten Things You Can Do to Pass the NAFTA Accountability Act</a><b><p>
</b><a href="cospons.html">The 109 NAFTA Accountability Act 
Co-Sponsors</a><b><p> 

</b><a href="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/activism/targets.html">Targets</a><b><p>

</b><a href="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/activism/factsheet.html">Factsheet</a><b><p>

</b><a href="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/activism/nafta-act.html">Text of the NAFTA Accountability Act</a><b><p>

</center>
<p>

</b>The NAFTA Accountability Act establishes a performance standard for the North American Free Trade
Agreement.  The bill requires that the President document that NAFTA has not made conditions worse
than before NAFTA. The areas to be examnined include trade between the U.S. and Mexico and Canada,
related jobs and wages, environmental and health conditions and illegal drug flow. <p>

If NAFTA can not pass such a "do no further harm" test in these area, then the President must conduct
renegotiations to fix specific problems. If the problems are not fixed, the bill provides for termination of
Congressional authorization of NAFTA.  Unless NAFTA were reauthorized by Congress, this would
trigger U.S. withdrawal from NAFTA.<p>

Currently, 108  Members of the House of Representatives have cosponsored the 
NAFTA Accountability
Act-- 66 Democrats, 40 Republicans and 2 independents. A number of these 
cosponsors had even voted for NAFTA. <p>

Since this bill is opposed by President Clinton and the Republican leadership, this legislation will likely
need to gather more than 200 cosponsors in order to get a vote.
<p>

<hr>
<p>
<P> Return to Public Citizen's <A HREF="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/">Global Trade Watch Page</A>

<p>

<P>Return to the <A HREF="http://www.citizen.org/public_citizen.html" IMG
SRC="http://www.citizen.org/images/pclogo.gif" HEIGHT=21 WIDTH=25 ALT="**"> 
Public Citizen Home Page.</A><p>
<HR>
<p>

Please send your comments and ideas on trade issues to:<ADDRESS> Public
Citizen's Global Trade Watch <A
HREF="mailto:pubcit_trade@citizen.org">&lt;pubcit_trade@citizen.org></A></ADDRESS><b><p>
</body>
</html>

