<PRE>
LATEST SURVEY OF FRENCH CITIZENS' VIEWS ON NUCLEAR POWER

The BVA Institute released its annual survey for 1995 focusing
on French public opinion and nuclear energy.  The survey is
important for France because nuclear power produces 80% of its
electricity.

Selected Questions from the BVA Institute Survey

Would you say nuclear power plants are polluting the rivers?     
Yes 48%   No 27%

Do you agree that nuclear power plants have considerably reduced
atmospheric pollution?   
Yes 30%   No 30%

Would you say that nuclear energy is better for the environment
than other energy sources?    
Yes 27%   No 35%

Do you agree that nuclear power plants are just like any other
plant?    
Yes 25%   No 65%

Do you agree that France could experience an accident as severe
as the Chernobyl accident?  
Yes 54%   No 29%

Would you say that French nuclear workers will experience some
health problems?    
Yes 76%   No 15%

Do you agree that France can safely store its radioactive
wastes?   
Yes 31%   No 38%

Do you think that it is very dangerous to live within 10 miles of
a nuclear power plant?   
Yes 65%   No 16%

Is the quality of information you have received concerning
nuclear industry and nuclear energy excellent?  
Yes 33%   No 59%

Do you believe that nuclear experts' explanations are extremely
hard to understand?      
Yes 67%   No 12%

Despite the French government's efforts in the last two decades
to promote nuclear energy, the results show that the French
people believe that nuclear reactors are not safe or
environmentally sound.

</PRE>
