<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Radioactive Waste Policy Congressional
Testimony
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#dd0000"
ALINK="#ff0000">
<BODY>
<H3>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>R</FONT>ADIOACTIVE <FONT SIZE=+2>W</FONT>ASTE <FONT
SIZE=+2>P</FONT>OLICY </Center></H3>
<P>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+1>Congressional Testimony</FONT>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/orgs/public_citizen/CMEP/radwaste/testimony.html">HIGH-LEVEL
RADIOACTIVE WASTE: MOVING IT AROUND WILL NOT SOLVE THE
PROBLEM</A>
<BR>March 2, 1995 -- Public Citizen's testimony to the U.S.
Senate Committee on Energy and Natural Resources on proposals to
amend the Nuclear Waste Policy Act.  Public Citizen opposes
efforts to weaken environmental standards and force an
unnecessary nuclear waste dump upon the state of Nevada.  A dump
in Nevada would open the door to transportation of highly toxic
nuclear waste on an unprecedented scale.</LI>
<P>
</UL>
