<UL>
<LI><B><I>
<A HREF="/orgs/public_citizen/CMEP/primer.html">
Renewable Energy 
Sourcebook: A Primer for Action (Section I)</A></I></B><BR>A
state-by-state 
study of renewable energy use, resource 
potential, policies, programs, and utility activities.  Each
state
profile
contains data for oil, coal, nuclear, natural gas, municipal
solid
waste, biomass, direct-use geothermal, geothermal electric,
geothermal heat pumps, solar thermal electric, solar hot water,
photovoltaics, and wind.  States are nationally ranked and
contain
detailed graphs and charts.  4/95, approx. 300 pages. 
<BR>[Item#CM-L040]
</LI><p>
<LI><B><I>
Single State Renewable Energy Profiles</I></B><BR>Contains
national
data,
introductory materials, and one state profile from the Renewable
Energy Sourcebook.<BR>4/95, approx. 35 pages.  [Item#CM-L040a]
</LI>
<p><LI><B><I>
State Energy Use and Renewable Resource Potential
Graphs</I></B><BR>
Electronic versions of the graphs used in each state profile of
the
Renewable Energy Sourcebook, detailing current energy use and
renewable resource potential.  Every state has six to eight
graphs.
All images in Encapsulated PostScript format (.eps) and available
for Macintosh [Item#CM-L040b] or PC-compatibles [Item#CM-L040c]. 
4/95.  
</LI>
<p>
<LI><B><I><A 
HREF="/orgs/public_citizen/CMEP/renewables/renewablesource.html"> 
The Renewable Source:  A National Directory of Resources,
Contacts,
and Companies</A></I></B>
<BR>A state-by-state listing of 2200 advocacy,
business, government, research, trade, and utility organizations
working with renewable energy systems and policies.  All entries
includes a contact name, address and phone number.  Most have
short
descriptions and fax numbers.  Some even include internet
addresses.  Entries are indexed by contact person, organization,
category and technology. 
<BR>8/94, 234 pages. [Item #CM-032]
</LI><P>
<LI><B><I>
Department of Energy Budget for Fiscal Year 1995</I></B>
<BR>Public Citizen's
testimony to the U.S. House of Representatives, Appropriations
Subcommittee on Energy and Waste Development, on renewable
energy,
nuclear power, and radioactive waste programs. 
<BR>3/94, 6 pages. [Item #CM-001]
</LI><P><LI><B><I>
A Sustainable Energy Blueprint and Budget</I></B>
<BR>A set of policy
recommendations presented to the Clinton administration by 100
environmental, consumer and business groups calling for steps to
reduce U.S. dependence on fossil fuels and increase reliance on
efficiency and renewable energy. 
<BR>1/93, Blueprint is 36 pages,
Budget-updated for FY95 is 45 pages.  [Item #CM-002]
</LI><P><LI><B><I>
The Power of the States: A Fifty-State Survey of Renewable
Energy</I></B>
<BR>
Provides a detailed, documented state-by-state survey of the
electricity and energy now provided by direct solar, wind,
hydroelectric, biomass and geothermal energy.  
<BR>6/90, 93 pages. [Item #CM-010]
</LI><P><LI><B><I>
The Power of the States: Supplement</I></B>
<BR>Contains the data sources
used as the basis for each number cited in the study.  
<BR>6/90, 105 pages. [Item #CM-011]  
</LI><LI>
Both the study and the supplement are available at a discount -
[Item #CM-012-a]
</LI><P><LI><B><I>
Power Surge</I></B>
<BR>Provides a pioneering review of the status and
near-term potential of renewable energy technologies which
already
provide 8% of U.S. energy needs at costs competitive with oil,
coal
and nuclear.  Includes detailed policy recommendations for
doubling
that contribution by the year 2000 to combat global warming.  
<BR>1989, 100 pages.  [Item #CM-012]
</LI>
</UL>
