<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Critical Mass Energy Policy List</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>
<H1><b><h2>CRITICAL MASS ENERGY PROJECT<br>
Energy Policy Listserver</h2></b></H1>
</BODY></HTML>
<hr><br>
<P>
Public Citizen operates an energy policy listserver to distribute action 
alerts on upcoming Congressional votes, summaries of recent legislative 
and executive branch actions and factsheets on topical issues.  We also 
distribute statements, press releases, and summaries of reports published 
by Public Citizen's Critical Mass Energy Project.  Specific topics 
covered include nuclear power, radioactive waste, fossil fuels, renewable 
energy, energy efficiency and transportation issues.<br> 
<P>
Members of advocacy groups, businesses, government agencies, utilities 
and individuals are encouraged to join the list.  Messages average one 
per week, though the frequency can be greater during peak legislative 
times.  This list is not interactive -- you will not be subject to a 
torrent of unsolicited postings and no messages will be sent to 
subscribers without the consent of Public Citizen.  In other words, the 
list will not facilitate a discussion of energy issues among subscribers, 
although we welcome your feedback on the content and quality of our 
postings.<br>
<P>
To join, email to listproc@essential.org and place the following in the message text:<br>
<P>
     <b>SUBSCRIBE CMEP-LIST [your name - organizational affiliation - home state]</b><br>
<P>
Example:<br>
<P>
     <b>SUBSCRIBE CMEP-LIST Matthew Freedman - Public Citizen - DC</b><br>
<P>
<i>Note: Your internet service provider is not an organizational 
affiliation (e.g. America Online).  If you are not connected with an 
group that works on energy issues, please write "individual" in this 
space.</i><br>
<P>
If you have specific questions about the list or problems subscribing, 
contact us at cmep@essential.org.<br>
<P>
<A HREF="/orgs/public_citizen/CMEP/subscribe.html">Return to the listserver subscription page<br></A>

<A HREF="/orgs/public_citizen/CMEP/home.html">Return to the Critical Mass Home Page<br></A>





