<BR>
<H2><CENTER><A NAME="WHATFOIC">THE FREEDOM OF INFORMATION
CLEARINGHOUSE
</A></CENTER></H2>
<P>    The Clearinghouse is a project of Ralph Nader's Center for
Study of Responsive Law. We provide technical and legal assistance
to individuals, public interest groups, and the media who seek
access to information held by government agencies. We are available
to consult by phone or mail. The Clearinghouse also litigates a
select number of cases each year to protect the public's right to
access government information. The Clearinghouse is a nonprofit
organization and welcomes your tax deductible contributions.<BR>
