 <h1><center>Press Release: For Immediate Release: June 19, 
1996</h1></center>							<p>

<p>

<b><center><p>

Clinton Administration Caves in to the WTO<p>

U.S. to Change Clean Air Act Regulations</b><p>

<p>

</center>
<center>Statement by Lori Wallach, Director of Public Citizen's Global Trade Watch<p>

 on the Clinton Administration's Decision to Alter Clean Air Act
Regulations to Obey a Ruling by the World Trade Organization<p>

</center>
<p>

	"Unfortunately this is exactly the outcome we predicted-- the United States caving
in and changing our environmental laws in the face of threatened trade sanctions. 
This decision by the Clinton Administration makes it even more obvious-- the
WTO needs to be changed, not the U.S. law."<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>


