<head>
<title>Trade Acronyms</title>
<meta name="Author" content="Common Machine#2">
<meta name="CreatedBy" content="WP Internet Publisher 6.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="c0d9d9">
<h1><center>Trade Acronyms</h1>
<p>

</center>
<b>AC</b>               -Andean Community (Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru, 
Venezuela)<p>

<b>ALADI</b>        -Latin American Integration Association<p>

<b>APEC</b>          -Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation Forum<p>

<b>CACM</b>        -Central American Common Market (Costa Rice, El Salvador, 
Guatemala,                  
                     Honduras, Nicaragua)<p>

<b>Caricom</b>      -Caribbean Community (Antigua and Barbuda, Bahamas, 
Barbados, Belize,                
                      Dominica, Guyana, Grenada, Jamaica, Montserrat, St. Kitts and Nevis, St. Lucia,     
                     St. Vincent and the Grenadines, Suriname, Trinidad and Tobago)<p>

<b>CET</b>             -Common External Tariff<p>

<b>ECLAC</b>       -Economic Commission for Latin America and the 
Caribbean<p>

<b>EU</b>               -European Union<p>

<b>FTAA</b>          -Free Trade Area of the Americas<a href="#*">*</a><p>

<b>GATT</b>          -General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade<p>

<b>GSP</b>             -Generalized System of Preferences<p>

<b>IDB</b>              -Inter-American Development Bank<p>

<b>INTAL</B>         -Institute for the Integration of Latin American and 
the Caribbean<p>

<b>ISIC</B>             -International Standard Industrial Classification<p>

<b>LAC</b>             -Latin America and the Caribbean<p>

<b>Mercosur</B>      -South Cone Common Market (Argentina, Brazil, 
Paraguay, Uruguay)<p>

<b>NAFTA</b>        -North American Free Trade Agreement (Canada, Mexico, 
United States)<p>

<b>OAS</b>             -Organization of American States<p>

<b>OECD</b>          -Organization for Economic Coordination and 
Development<p>

<b>RTC</b>             -Regional Technical Cooperation<p>

<b>SIECA</b>         -Permanent Secretariat of the General Treaty of Central 
American Economic              
                     Integration<p>

<b>TRAINS</b>      -Trade Information System<p>

<b>UNCTAD</b>    -United Nations Conference on Trade and Development<p>

<b>WTO</b>           -World Trade Organization <p>

<hr>
<a href="http://www.citizen.org/gtw">Return to the Global Trade Watch 
Home Page</a><p><hr>

<a name=*>*The acronym FTAA refers to the 34 countries of the Hemisphere 
that 
are signatories to the Presidential Declaration of the Miami Summit.  
</body>
</html>
