<head>
<title>Public Citizen: Ten Things You
Can Do to Pass the NAFTA
Accountability Act</title>
<meta name="CreatedBy" content="WP Internet Publisher 6.1">
</head>
<body>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#0000ff"
VLINK="#dd0000" A LINK="#ff0000"><p>

<p>

<center><p>

<h1>Ten Things You Can Do to Pass the
NAFTA Accountability Act</h1>
</center>
1.   <b>Convince your Senators and Member of the House of Representatives to cosponsor
the NAFTA Accountability Act. </b>.<a href="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/activism/conglet.html"> Sample Letter to Congress</a>, <a href="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/activism/coalition.html">Sample Coalition Letter;</a> If
your Members of Congress are already Cosponsors, then please thank them for their support. <p>

2.  <b>Help convince top targeted Members of the House of Representatives to cosponsor
the NAFTA Accountability Act.</b> <a href="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/activism/targets.html">Targets</a> Since President Clinton, House Speaker Newt
Gingrich, and Senate Majority Leader Bob Dole all oppose this legislation, we will need 200+
Members of the House of Representatives to Cosponsor this legislation in order to force a
vote. When a targeted Member signs on to the NAFTA Accountability Act we will put
another in his or her place until we get a vote on the bill.<a 
href="cospons.html">See the current list of co-sponsors</a><p>

3.  <b>Send a letter to the editor </b><a href="http://www.novell.com/#Editor"></a><b>to your local newspaper.</b>  The Letters to the Editor section of
a newspaper is generally one of the most read sections.  You can also submit letters to the
editor to national magazines. <a href="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/activism/editlet.html">Sample Letter to the Editor</a><p>

4. <b>Write an opinion article for your local newspaper (also known as op-ed).</b>  Many
newspapers will print an opinion article which is much longer than a letter to the editor (400-800 words, depending on the newspaper). <a href="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/activism/actoped.html">Sample Opinion Article</a><a href="http://www.novell.com/




#Op-Ed"></a><p>

5.  <b>Get 5 Friends to contacts the Targets as well as their own Members of Congress</b>;<p>

6.   If you are a member of an activist organization, such as an environmental organization,
labor union, church group, student society, farm club etc., <b>get your organization to send a
letter to the Members of the House and Senate from your state</b>. <a href="http://www.citizen.org/pctrade/activism/coalition.html">Sample Coalition Letter</a><p>

 7.<a href="http://www.novell.com/#Sam,ple letter"></a>  <b>Spread the word on the NAFTA Accountability Act through talk radio.  </b>Call in to
talk shows and mention the NAFTA Accountability Act and give out the Congressional
Switchboard phone number (202)225-3121. Call radio talk show producers and ask them to do
a show on NAFTA and the NAFTA Accountability Act.<p>

8.   <b>Ask representatives of your local government to help put the pressure on
Representatives and Senators from your state. </b><p>

9.  <b>Subscribe to Global Trade Watch's Activist list serve on the internet.</b> Receive activist
alerts, press releases and legislative updates.<p>

10.  <b>Support Public Citizen's Global Trade Watch</b><p>

Founded by Ralph Nader in 1971, Public Citizen is a nonprofit citizen research, lobbying and
litigation organization based in Washington D.C.  Global Trade Watch works to promote the
needs and interests of citizens in international trade agreements in every public forum:
Congress, the courts, government agencies, and the news media.  In addition, Public Citizen
produces and distributes extensive materials on how international trade agreements affect
food, health and safety, jobs and wages, the environment and the democratic process.<p>

<hr>
<p>

<p>
<a href="http://www.citizen.org/pcjoin.html#Join PC">Join Public 
Citizen</a>  and begin making a difference today.    <p>
