<HEAD><TITLE>News,and visitors, European University Institute (Florence, IT)
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000"><CENTER> <H1><IMG
ALIGN="left" SRC="../iue.gif">
<BR>European University Institute,
<BR>Florence, Italy
<BR> News and visitors</H1>
</CENTER>
<HR> On Monday 2 December, the President of the Italian Republic, Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro, was in Florence for a visit to the European University Institute.
Further information is available in a
<A HREF="scalDE.html">Presseerkl&auml;rung</A>,
<A HREF="scalEN.html">press release</A>,
<A HREF="scalFR.html">communiqu&eacute de presse</A> and
<A HREF="scalIT.html">comunicato stampa</A>.
<HR>On 28 November 1996 Prof Hans Tietmeyer, President of the Deutsche 
Bundesbank delivered the 19th Jean Monnet Lecture, entitled 
"The European Economy poised Between Global Markets and Internal Challenges".
Further information is available in a
<A HREF="tietmeyerDE.html">Presseerkl&auml;rung</A>,
<A HREF="tietmeyerEN.html">press release</A>,
<A HREF="tietmeyerFR.html">communiqu&eacute de presse</A> and
<A HREF="tietmeyerIT.html">comunicato stampa</A>.
The full text of his lecture is available in 
<A HREF="tietspeechDE.html">German</A> and in 
<A HREF="tietspeechEN.html">English</A>.
<HR>
On Thursday, 31 October 1996, Prof Mario Monti gave a lecture at the 
European University Institute.
For further information see the 
<A HREF="montiEN.html">press release</A> and 
<A HREF="montiIT.html">comunicato stampa</A>.
<HR>
At the request and with funding of the European Parliament, the
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/RSC/Welcome.html">Robert
Schuman Centre</A> at the European University Institute, Florence (in
collaboration with the <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/AEL/Welcome.html">Academy of
European Law</A>), has established, with the support of eminent European
Community law experts, a unified and simplified version of the European
Communities Treaties (EC Treaty, ECSC Treaty, EURATOM Treaty) and the Treaty on
European Union.
For further information see the 
<A HREF="treatyEN.html">press release</A>, 
<A HREF="treatyFR.html">Communiqu&eacute de Presse</A>, and
<A HREF="treatyIT.html">comunicato stampa</A>.
<HR>
A group of sixteen researchers of the European University Institute will
be participating in the Italian contingent of the 
<A HREF="albania.html">monitoring mission</A> 
for the elections in Albania.
<HR>
The European University Institute celebrates its 20th Anniversary this academic
year. During the year there will be various events to mark this significant
anniversary.
On Friday 27 September we will be having the first 
<strong>Conferring Ceremony
</strong> of the EUI doctorate. The ceremony will take place in the church of
the Badia Fiesolana, admittance will commence at 3 pm and the actual degree 
awarding ceremony will begin at 3:30 pm.
More detailed information is contained in a <A HREF="ceremEN.html">press 
statement</A>/
<A HREF="ceremIT.html">comunicato stampa</A>.
<HR> 
The President of the Republic of Portugal, Mr. Jorge Sampaio,  
<A HREF="sampindex.html">visited</A>  the Institute on Wednesday, 25 September
1996.
<HR>
On 1 July 1996 <STRONG> Prof. Gil Carlos Rodr&iacute;guez Iglesias,
President of the European Court of Justice,</STRONG> gave a lecture (<A
HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/iglesI.html">comunicato stampa</A>) within the
framework of the 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/AEL/Welcome.html">Academy of European Law</A>. 
<HR>
On 27 and 28 June 1996 <STRONG>Dr. Klaus H&auml;nsch,  President of the
European Parliament,</STRONG>  visited the European University Institute (<A
HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/haenschit.html">comunicato stampa</A>), and gave
the <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/AEL/haensch.html">Robert Schuman  Lecture</A> &quot;Reasserting
the political will to move Europe forward&quot;  within the framework of the 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/AEL/Welcome.html">Academy of European Law</A>. 
<HR>
On Monday, 24 June 1996 the <STRONG>High-Level Panel on the free movement
of persons (known as the Veil Group)</STRONG>  met for two days at the  European
University Institute. (<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/veileng.html">press
release</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/veilf.html">communiqu&eacute; de presse</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/veilit.html">comunicato stampa</A>),
<HR>
On Thursday, 20 June 1996, on the eve of the European Council in Florence,
the<STRONG> President of the Council of Ministers, Prof. Romano Prodi</STRONG>,
visited the European University Institute, and spoke on prospects for the  
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/prodiindex.html">future of Europe</A>. The
speech is available in English, French and Italian.
<HR>
<ADDRESS>
European University Institute, last updated on 2 December 1996,
<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:webmaster@www.iue.it">webmaster@www.iue.it</A>
</ADDRESS>
<HR>
<P><A HREF="http://www.iue.it">European University Institute</A></P>
</BODY>
</HTML>
