<TITLE>New on the server - European University Institute, Florence, Italy</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000">
<IMG
ALIGN="left" SRC="http://www.iue.it/iue.gif" ALT="European University Institute logo" HEIGHT="116" WIDTH="110">
<CENTER><H1>New on the server</H1>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<STRONG>The European University Institute is extending and reorganizing the
services it offers on the WWW, both externally and internally. We specially
welcome all suggestions and comments! e-mail:
<A HREF="mailto:webmaster@www.iue.it">webmaster@www.iue.it</A></STRONG>
<HR>
The EUI homepage has been reorganized. This is an intermediary solution. Let
us have comments!
<HR>
The economics department now makes it's detailed
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ECO/week.html">weekly program</A> available.

<HR> On Monday 2 December, the President of the Italian Republic, Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro, was in Florence for a visit to the European University Institute.
Further information is available in a
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/scalDE.html">Presseerkl&auml;rung</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/scalEN.html">press release</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/scalFR.html">communiqu&eacute de presse</A> and
<A HREF=" http://www.iue.it/ANN/scalIT.html">comunicato stampa</A>.
<HR>On 28 November 1996 Prof Hans Tietmeyer, President of the Deutsche 
Bundesbank delivered the 19th Jean Monnet Lecture, entitled 
"The European Economy poised Between Global Markets and Internal Challenges".
Further information is available in a
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/tietmeyerDE.html">Presseerkl&auml;rung</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/tietmeyerEN.html">press release</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/tietmeyerFR.html">communiqu&eacute de presse</A> and
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/tietmeyerIT.html">comunicato stampa</A>.
The full text of his lecture is available in 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/tietspeechDE.html">German</A> and in 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/tietspeechEN.html">English</A>.
<HR>
Finally - something different!
The <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/General/Internal/BF/Welcome.html">Bar
Fiasco</A> is going online. Pages provided by and in responsibility of the 
Bar Fiasco Committee (EUI members only).
<HR>
The <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/General/Internal/phonelist.html">internal 
phone numbers</A> are now available - EUI members only.
<HR>
On Thursday, 31 October 1996, Prof Mario Monti gave a lecture at the 
European University Institute.
For further information see the 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/montiEN.html">press release</A> and 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/montiIT.html">comunicato stampa</A>.
<HR>
At the request and with funding of the European Parliament, the
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/RSC/Welcome.html">Robert
Schuman Centre</A> at the European University Institute, Florence (in
collaboration with the <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/AEL/Welcome.html">Academy of
European Law</A>), has established, with the support of eminent European
Community law experts, a unified and simplified version of the 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it./RSC/TREATY/Welcome.html">European 
Communities Treaties</A> 
(EC Treaty, ECSC Treaty, EURATOM Treaty) and the Treaty on
European Union.
For further information see the 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/treatyEN.html">press release</A>, 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/treatyFR.html">Communiqu&eacute de Presse</A>, and
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/treatyIT.html">comunicato stampa</A>.
<HR>
A group of sixteen researchers of the European University Institute will
be participating in the Italian contingent of the <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/albania.html">monitoring mission</A> 
for the elections in Albania.
<HR>
Antivirus software can now be 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/CDC/Institute.internal/Welcome.html">downloaded</A> 
from the web-server - EUI members only!
Release 224 (September 1996) available.
<HR>
On Friday 27 September the first 
<strong>Conferring Ceremony
</strong> of the EUI doctorate took place, part of the festivities for the 20th
Anniversary of the Institute. 
More detailed information is contained in a 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/ceremEN.html">press 
statement</A>/
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/ceremIT.html">comunicato stampa</A>.
<HR>
The President of the Republic of Portugal, Mr. Jorge Sampaio,  
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/sampindex.html">visited</A> 
the Institute on Wednesday, 25 September 1996.
<HR>
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/CDC/Institute.internal/Welcome.html">News from 
the Computing Service</A> have been distributed by e-mail - 
for further reference they also will remain available on our internal 
web-server.
<HR>
On an experimental basis the full text of two Working Papers of the Robert 
Schuman Centre can now be 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/PUB/Wpapers/Welcome.html">downloaded</A> 
as postscript files.
<HR>
The information on the <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/RSC/Welcome.html">Robert 
Schuman Centre</A> has been updated and extended.<HR>
A short <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/General/Welcome.html">description of the
Institute</A> should give visitors to the site an overview - also a step in the
direction of more multi-lingual services (the Institute languages still missing
will follow soon).
<HR>
The <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/PUB/Welcome.html">EUI publications</A> page
has been extended, reorganized and updated. It includes now complete lists of
all working papers, information on the H&amp;C Yearbook, new monographs, and
pointers to other EUI publications. The working papers list can also be
downloaded as a postscript file.
<HR>
The Institute's <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/Servac/acserhp.htm">Academic
service</A> now provides information on application procedures and grants for
postdoctoral researchers (including downloadable forms), insurance,
accomodation, and other practical matters.
<HR>
The <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/EF/proj97.html">European Forum theme</A> for
1997/98 will be "International
Migrations: Geography, Politics, and Culture in Europe and Beyond". It will
be directed by Professors Christian Joppke (EUI, Department of Social and
Political Sciences) and Ren&eacute; Leboutte (EUI, Department of History and
Civilization). These pages also contain information on application on grants for
Forum fellowships.
<HR>
The <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/AEL/Welcome.html">Academy of European Law</A>
pages have been reorganized and updated. This includes updates for the European
Journal of International Law and the Collected Courses of the AEL.
<HR>
The Newsletter of the <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/WGES/Welcome.html">Working
Group of Environmental studies</A> now also includes issues 14 and 15.
<HR>
On 27 and 28 June 1996 Dr. Klaus H&auml;nsch,  President of the European
Parliament,  gave the <A HREF="http://www.iue.it/AEL/haensch.html">Robert
Schuman  Lecture</A> &quot;Reasserting the political will to move Europe forward&quot;
 within the framework of the 
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/AEL/Welcome.html">Academy of European Law</A>. 
<HR>
On Thursday, 20 June 1996, on the eve of the European Council in Florence,
the President of the Council of Ministers, Prof. Romano Prodi spoke on prospects
for the  
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/ANN/prodiindex.html">future of Europe</A>. The
speech is available in English, French and Italian.
<HR>
