<HR> 
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.iue.it/">The European University Institute </A>(EUI) is a
postgraduate research institute set up in 1976 by the Member States of the
European Union. The EUI, which is located in Fiesole, Florence, consists of four
academic departments: Economics; History and Civilisation; Law; and Political
and Social Sciences, supported by administrative, computing and library staff.
The research students of the EUI are drawn mainly from the graduates of
universities in the Member States, though some students come from Eastern
European countries, and a small number of students come to EUI from outside
Europe. Special grants from the member states, private institutions and the EUI
provide financial support for most graduate students. The academic staff of the
EUI are appointed on fixed term contracts (of maximum length four years and with
one renewal possible), and are usually on leave from their home institution.
</P>
<P>
We provide in above a description of the programme of studies in the Economics
Department, including a list of the current teaching staff and their research
interests. Further information about the EUI and application procedures is
contained in the Institute's General Prospectus which is available from:
</P>
<P>
</P>
